https://prez.dev/description.@value: The coordinate reference systems (geographic and projected) used and referred to within Western Australia. It includes historical and current reference systems, Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) zones, and, where applicable, notations based on the EPSG registry (https://epsg.io/). Some concepts are included to account for legacy data/maps with limited information.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: The standard map projection associated with GDA94 is the Map Grid of Australia 1994 (MGA94), a transverse Mercator projection that conforms to the internationally standardized Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) grid system. At that time the recommended reference ellipsoid was also changed from ANS to the Geodetic Reference System 1980 (GRS80) ellipsoid. Area of use: Australia including Lord Howe Island, Macquarie Island, Ashmore and Cartier Islands, Christmas Island, Cocos (Keeling) Islands, Norfolk Island; all onshore and offshore.

https://prez.dev/description.@value: The standard map projection associated with GDA94 is the Map Grid of Australia 1994 (MGA94), a transverse Mercator projection that conforms to the internationally standardized Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) grid system. At that time the recommended reference ellipsoid was also changed from ANS to the Geodetic Reference System 1980 (GRS80) ellipsoid. Area of use: Australia including Lord Howe Island, Macquarie Island, Ashmore and Cartier Islands, Christmas Island, Cocos (Keeling) Islands, Norfolk Island; all onshore and offshore.

The accompanying national map projection to MGA94, a transverse Mercator projection that conforms to zone 49 of the internationally accepted Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) grid system. Area of use for MGA94 zone 49: Australia - onshore and offshore west of 114° E; Christmas Island - offshore east of 108°E.

The accompanying national map projection to MGA94, a transverse Mercator projection that conforms to zone 50 of the internationally accepted Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) grid system. Area of use for MGA94 zone 50: Australia – onshore and offshore between 114°E and 120°E.

The accompanying national map projection to MGA94, a transverse Mercator projection that conforms to zone 51 of the internationally accepted Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) grid system. Area of use for MGA94 zone 51: Australia – onshore and offshore between 120°E and 126°E.

The accompanying national map projection to MGA94, a transverse Mercator projection that conforms to zone 52 of the internationally accepted Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) grid system. Area of use for MGA94 zone 52: Australia – onshore and offshore between 126°E and 132°E.
